[PATCH] adbd: disable ADB_TRACE in minimal mode

Disable ADB tracing support when ADBD_MINIMAL is defined.
This removes:
- Debug tracing code and macros
- Trace mask handling
- Mutex for trace output locking
- Reduces code size and removes runtime overhead

The tracing functionality is mainly useful for development
and debugging, but adds unnecessary overhead for production
embedded systems with limited resources.

Usage: Add -DADBD_MINIMAL to CPPFLAGS when building adbd

Signed-off-by: Buildroot User <user@example.com>
---
 core/adb/adb.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/core/adb/adb.h b/core/adb/adb.h
index abcd123..efgh456 100644
--- a/core/adb/adb.h
+++ b/core/adb/adb.h
@@ -340,7 +340,11 @@ int backup_service(BackupOperation operation, char* args);
 
 /* define ADB_TRACE to 1 to enable tracing support, or 0 to disable it */
 
+#ifdef ADBD_MINIMAL
+#define  ADB_TRACE    0
+#else
 #define  ADB_TRACE    1
+#endif
 
